jurisdiction.title: Yeshivah of Flatbush Joel Braverman High School

437A5661DD7647FB9610B31874498643.description: I take an active part in my learning, seeking out the information that I need to succeed and staying on top of all deadlines and expectations.

3879D3BEDD914718ABAD3D16D6D42062.description: I meet most deadlines, though I may need reminders. I follow instructions.

BA20467C9E3844EEA4EA656D58B8BBE0.description: Demonstrate successful student habits: meet deadlines, read and follow instructions, ask questions, seek help and support, and manage digital tools and digital spaces effectively to keep track of work.

5CD46D35A7984547B20B3F8B552122D6.description: I document my process so that I can see and demonstrate my growth. My Learning Log is a place where I review my learning and find new ways of thinking.

3DB555DEFA2B4557A7BC217F4ED8E9AF.description: I use my Learning Log to identify ways that I’ve grown and developed. My reflections show that I try to push my thinking.

C24D9DC4869D41FA873F28A1F67C8E33.description: I keep a record of my learning process by choosing specific photos, videos, drawings, or notes. My Learning Log reflections demonstrate critical thinking and depth.

E52179D8C8914F08AE932109879769AE.description: I keep a record of most learning activities through photos, videos, drawings, or notes. I answer the reflection questions in my Learning Log.

04909D81EC354B789C93CBB925F1A089.description: Document learning and growth: maintain the weekly Learning Log by taking lots of photos and videos, drawing sketches, and writing copious notes to document the learning process, and then reflecting to show growth and development.

62CA4AB1C3204FDF95DB1DA32015DBC9.description: I understand that failure is part of the learning process, and look for opportunities to take learning risks. I have coping strategies that help me push through challenges.

E19117A784C44C18BBF16AD8A4F39ED7.description: I can find some patterns in my frustrations and failures, and I am beginning to use those to help guide my learning.

23186414E86843F98A792736AE912394.description: I sometimes feel like giving up, but through keeping track of failures and frustrations, I know some strategies that help me push through.

98BC3DD97C0F4010BA9B7C8CC5800DE3.description: I can list my frustrations and failures in my Learning Log. I get frustrated by failure, but with encouragement I keep trying.

CF263CD58DA840D59AA2C178661A4DC8.description: Fail forward: develop strategies to manage frustrations and failures while working on programs and projects, exhibit tenacity by continuing to work even harder when things get difficult.

1D2E0662031F4878B196B4B1AF7373D7.description: I  am an active community member who works closely with my team members and classmates to produce high quality work in response to feedback. I take ownership of classroom spaces.

02DE9F54B6DB4314A84FAEA3BA792380.description: I provide valuable feedback to my classmates by utilizing the Feedback Templates and considering what kind of feedback would be helpful for me. I look for opportunities to collaborate with peers.

94926B04B5F64796863B7207A674FA77.description: I ask for feedback from my classmates at important stages in my project. My classmates indicate that I am a valued team member in peer reviews. I leave the room organized / neat.

3D0DB5748FEC459B90F082CFBF748DFA.description: I can give feedback and work with peers when it’s part of a class activity. I show respect by leaving the room organized/neat.

FF7CA43ADF3D45C0979F6C6BF91F98CE.description: Be a positive community member: provide high-quality feedback to others and seek out feedback for your work, participate in small-group and whole-group work, and move through our classroom spaces with kindness and respect.

449A7890FD0745DD94CD67D264FCFD7F.description: I can successfully choose a tool to create for a project and use it independently in a safe and effective manner. I have shown that I can use and maintain 3+ fabrication tools in the Makerspace.

E7918DFDF11A46E582CEFFB2D0958B96.description: I have shown that I can use and maintain 3+ fabrication tools in the Makerspace. I can have a conversation about the best tool for a specific purpose, but I may need some help choosing.

1FFBF2104F1240258B27B2A110795EF2.description: I have shown that I can use and maintain 1-2 fabrication tools in the Makerspace. I have some ideas about projects that I could use the tools for.

BF390AC39A9E4B65997A5B05B8A98EC1.description: I know what fabrication tools are available to me in the Makerspace. I know where to find more information about the fabrication tools.

0924CC36DF0D4CB0BA82840C15B6C2DB.description: Intentionally use fabrication tools to enhance projects and/or create other products, use materials correctly, safely, and keep them organized.

9A2FCB517E9B432B829739109D72614B.description: I can independently solve problems as they come up in my circuits or code by relying on a variety of troubleshooting skills.

CFF2B97CA0EF409D841657EC5A14D48A.description: I always troubleshoot first or consult with classmates before going to my teacher for help. I use the mistakes that I make to guide my next steps.

45A659D0768C4365B74A9B24013D1CE0.description: I know which steps to take when I encounter a problem in my code or in my circuits. I know where to look for information about new components/sensors.

F8A4FE8E7419425BB46B3125AD2A8CAF.description: I can identify error messages and know which debugging tools are available for me to use. I can search for solutions online, but I may not know how to choose the right one.

FD9F84794E144439ACDBC0C5FD0B88F5.description: Solve problems independently: find information both online and in print and use error messages and debugging skills to solve the problems in your code.

8B0A7395076C45C1866A778D8E9E7069.description: I “do engineering” by iterating on my electrical circuits and computer programs to add complexity and efficiency.

0D6BFBCB854048E08A92B0138C088EDD.description: I can add complexity to my circuits and programs when instructed to do so and with some support.

8529DBE17AB348AEA95F66682FD4270B.description: I can build basic circuits and write basic programs independently or with limited support.

4DBBDCF3511F43EAB192B1507E4B6313.description: I can identify and explain the basics of electrical circuits and/or Arduino code. I still need a lot of support to build and write.

5EFCBBDF5D6D4BD7A61F69D382B2B8D7.description: Develop engineering skills by creating electrical circuits and writing computer programs of increasing complexity.

7B306AB461464673BE119F833A3D9A92.description: I cycle through the stages of Design Thinking to push my thinking and keep me connected to my user. I ask thoughtful questions and look for opportunities to iterate.

648B3678DBB24FC9B136EB3508AA00B5.description: I can independently move through the stages of the Design Thinking process in order to build a solution that helps a specific user.

B90959B3DAE344A6BFDF87D91939F954.description: I fully participate in Design Thinking activities in class. I use the stages of the process to build solutions that help specific users.

878C25B603744B33B2D9D38690D047AD.description: I can identify and explain the stages of Design Thinking.

98BF3B2DB37E4C94A9C1BEF906F051DE.description: Use the Design Thinking process to ask research-informed questions, brainstorm multiple solutions, prototype rapidly, test chosen solutions, and iterate on the process.
